# GPU server — track only the artefacts that need to be in version control.
#
# Forge on-demand pod boot uses the volume-bootstrap pattern: the four
# files below are scp'd onto the network volume by bootstrap-volume.sh
# (which itself runs from a developer's laptop, never the VPS). The
# legacy always-on pod's startup.sh is kept tracked too because it pre-
# dates this work and is referenced by /workspace/config/ on RunPod.
# Everything else (server.py, model_registry.py, credentials notes,
# the original Dockerfile) stays untracked.
gpu-server/*
!gpu-server/handler.py
!gpu-server/serve.py
!gpu-server/startup.sh
!gpu-server/forge-startup.sh
!gpu-server/forge-requirements.txt
!gpu-server/bootstrap-volume.sh
